Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, has lambasted President Muhammadu Buhari for reintegrating former Boko Haram terrorists into Nigeria. He accused the President of pampering the terrorists and risking the lives of many other Nigerians. Kanu stated this in reaction to the graduation and reintegration of 601 repentant Boko Haram members into the society. Recall that the ex-fighters reintegrated into the society included those from Cameroon, Chad and Niger. The Coordinator, Operation Safe Corridor, Major General Bamidele Shafa made the announcement on Saturday. In a tweet, Kanu wrote: “No nation ever PAMPERS terrorists. @MBuhari’s Nigeria not only pampers terrorists but it gives them scholarships and sends them to mix with those they’ve terrorized and slaughtered. “There’s no other way of looking at this than that Nigeria is the ONLY nation that rewards TERRORISM.” Source The Indigenous Peoples of Biafra(IPOB) has insisted the Army cannot stop its members from attending the burial of parents of its founder, Nnamdi Kanu. The outlawed group dared soldiers to stop its members if they can at the funeral slated for February 14 at Isiama Afaraukwu community in Abia State.… February 6, 2020 In "News" The Defence Headquarters has declared IPOB a terrorist organisation. Now that was long overdue. Albeit it is better late than never. You can't call a sovereign nation a zoo, her president a pedophile, a plastic reconstructed sudanese, threaten to go for his head in Abuja, call on Nigerians to boycott… September 16, 2017 In "Social Media Feeds" Mohammad Tawhidi, popularly known as Imam of Peace, has led a social media campaign for the arrest of President Muhammadu Buhari over the rising insecurity in the country and the government’s decision to free repentant Boko Haram terrorists. The Muslim influencer and reformist Imam is leading the campaign with the… July 25, 2020 In "News"